Paramid: eParamID_RecordingShareSMBDialect
Type: Enum
Menu Number: 86.43
Name: SMB Dialect
Description: Selects a specific version of the Server Message Block (SMB) protocol to use with a remote SMB share, or allows automatic negotiation of the highest available version. Start with 'auto' unless you experience long connection delays (two minutes or more) or if you must connect to a server that only supports SMB1 (also called CIFS or SMB with no version number), such as Mac OS X 10.8 Mountain Lion or earlier. WARNING: CIFS/SMB1 is insecure and should be avoided if at all possible. Use of CIFS/SMB1 may expose sensitive user credentials in the clear to anyone listening on your network.
Access: Read/Write
Persistence: false
Preset: false
Min: 1
Max: 8
Default: 2
Enumerations:
Value: "1"
Text: "Auto"
Value: "2"
Text: "SMB 1.0"
Value: "3"
Text: "SMB 2.0"
Value: "4"
Text: "SMB 2.1"
Value: "5"
Text: "SMB 3.0"
